com.nokia.places

Interface Page

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    EditorialPage, ImagePage, ResultPage, ReviewPage

    public interface Page
    This interface defines a basis for a paginated collection. Pagination is is the process of dividing content into discrete pages of information. The response to a request does not return a complete set of results, but holds a page containing a subset of the results. Additional results can be obtained by requesting further results pages.
    See Also:
    Nokia's Restful Places API - paginated collections

    • Method Detail

      • hasNextPage

        boolean hasNextPage()
        This method retrieves a boolean value indicating whether or not the page has further items available on a subsequent page.
        Returns:
        true if the page has further items available, false otherwise.

      • getTotalAvailableItemCount

        java.lang.Integer getTotalAvailableItemCount()
        This method retrieves the total number of items available for a place. For example, if a place has 50 images and no other items, the return value of a call to this method would be 50.

        Note: It is not always possible to calculate the total number of elements in a collection. The attribute, therefore, might be missing, or might contain just an estimate. Instead of relying on the presence of the attribute, clients must rely on the existence of the next attribute to find out if additional items are available.

        Returns:
        The total number of available items (could be null).

      • getOffsetCount

        java.lang.Integer getOffsetCount()
        This method retrieves the index number of the first item in the current page.

        Pages other than the first page of a collection may include the attribute that this method gets, which contains the index of the first item in the current page.

        Returns:
        The index number of the first item in the current page for the entire collection (could be null).
